  "description": "# Sejong (40km×40km)\r\n\r\n### SEJ4 · v0.1.0\r\n\r\nCustom map of Sejong, Korea made with official Korean traffic volume data from official soures.\r\nWith 7,551 Pops and 1,236,542 population\r\n\r\n## Coverage\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width: auto\">\r\n<tr><td><strong>Region</strong></td><td>Sejong, Daejeon, Cheongju </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td><strong>Playable Area</strong></td><td>1,600 km²</td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n## Population Summary\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width: auto\">\r\n<tr><td><strong>Total Modeled Demand</strong></td><td align=\"right\">1,236,542</td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n## Additional Features\r\n\r\n- **Neighborhood Labels** — The map includes municipal and neighborhood labels derived from administrative boundary data.\r\n\t- 시도 (Si, Do - Metropolitan / Provincial level)\r\n\t- 시군구 (Si, Gun, Gu - City / County / District level)\r\n\t- 읍면동 (Eup, Myeon, Dong - Neighborhood level)\r\n\r\n## Data Sources\r\n\r\n- Korean Transportation Database (Korea Transport Institute, KOTI) (ktdb.go.kr)\r\n- V-world (Ministry of Land, Infrastructure and Transport, MOLIT) (vworld.kr)\r\n- Statistical Geographic Information System (SGIS) plus (Ministry of Data and Statistics, MODS) (sgis.mods.go.kr)\r\n- Address-based Industry Support Service (Ministry of the Interior and Safety, MOIS) (business.juso.go.kr)\r\n\r\n## Credits\r\n\r\nMap authored by Budha",
